<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<text id="WB_KL-75">
    <metadata>
        <title>"Soaking Acorns"</title>
        <author>Julia <alph>Starritt</alph></author>
        <date>1957</date>
        <publication>William Bright, <em>The Karok Language</em> (1957), pp. 288-289, Text
            75</publication>
    </metadata>
    <data>
        <paragraph>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w gl="soaked acorns"><m id="4408">pá</m><m id="4824">piish</m></w>
                    <w gl="they make"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="2348">ikyâa</m><m id="6035"
                        >ti</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6307">uum</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
                    <w gl="they soak acorns"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="4827">píishha</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>When they made píish, they soaked acorns.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w><m id="4978">píshiip</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6307">uum</m></w>
                    <w gl="edge of water"><m id="2940">ishahá</m><m id="6047">tiimich</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
                    <w gl="they dig a hole"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="2914">'íripkuri</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5505">su'vári</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>And first they dug a deep hole at the edge of the water.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3745">kári</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6383">vaa</m></w>
                    <w gl="the acorn"><m id="4407">pa</m><m id="6907">xuntápan</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3670">káan</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
                    <w gl="they pour in"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="3632">iyváy</m><m id="4022"
                            >kurih</m><m id="6380">va</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>Then they poured the acorns in there.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="1361">hâari</m></w>
                    <w gl="five basket-loads"><m id="3412">itroopa</m><m id="801">'átiv</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>
                    <w><m id="1361">hâari</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3974">kumatêeshich</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>Sometimes there were five basket-loads and sometimes more.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="5163">púyava</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3745">kári</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
                    <w gl="they cover"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="3329">íthxup</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5264">sákriiv</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>
                    <w gl="little logs"><m id="2146">ikuka</m><m id="6128">tunvêech</m><m id="584"
                            >as</m></w>
                    <w><m id="4281">múuk</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>Then they covered it tightly with little logs.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w gl="big rocks"><m id="583">asá</m><m id="3668">kaam</m><m id="5201"
                        >sa</m></w>
                    <w><m id="4281">mûuk</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
                    <w gl="they put on"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="3560">iyáakoo</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>And they put them on with big rocks.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="5163">púyava</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6675">vúra</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3670">káan</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5502">sú'</m></w>
                    <w gl="it piles into"><m id="6175">u</m><m id="2019">krítumkuri</m></w>
                    <w><m id="1361">hâari</m></w>
                    <w gl="all year"><m id="3217">itha</m><m id="1373">hárinay</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w><m id="1361">hâari</m></w>
                    <w gl="longer time"><m id="3970">kumá</m><m id="6839">xara</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>So (the acorns) were piled in there, sometimes a year and sometimes
                    longer.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="5163">púyava</m></w>
                    <w gl="when it tastes good"><m id="4408">pa</m><m id="5506">t</m><m id="6175"
                            >u</m><m id="332">'amayâ</m><m id="1358">ahaak</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3745">kári</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
                    <w gl="they eat"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="814">'av</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>And when they became good-tasting, then they ate them.</eng>
            </s>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="4978">píshiip</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
                    <w gl="they strain out"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="2674">ip</m><m id="5737"
                            >táthrip</m></w>
                    <w gl="big plate baket"><m id="2589">imvarám</m><m id="3668">kaam</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>First they strained them with a big tray-basket.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w gl="in burden basket"><m id="789">atimna</m><m id="3660">k</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
                    <w gl="they pour in"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="3623">íyvaayramnih</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>And they poured them in a burden basket.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="5163">púyava</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
                    <w gl="they boil"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="4561">páramva</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>Then they boiled them.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w gl="when"><m id="4408">pa</m><m id="5506">t</m><m id="6175">óo</m></w>
                    <w gl="when cooked"><m id="2565">mtúpa</m><m id="1358">haak</m></w>
                    <w><m id="6847">xás</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3745">kári</m></w>
                    <w><m id="5506">tá</m></w>
                    <w gl="they eat"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="814">'av</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>When they were done, they ate them.</eng>
            </s>
            <s>
                <kar>
                    <w><m id="2487">impúukach</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w gl="they will eat"><m id="3977">kun</m><m id="814">'áv</m><m id="1379"
                            >eesh</m></w>
                    <w><m id="3752">káru</m></w>
                    <w><m id="768">áthiik</m></w>. </kar>
                <eng>They would eat them either warm or cold.</eng>
            </s>
        </paragraph>
    </data>
